President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. has declared a major disaster in the state of Vermont due to severe storm and flooding that occurred from December 22 to December 24, 2022. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available to state and eligible local governments, as well as certain private nonprofit organizations, for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. The counties of Chittenden, Essex, Franklin, Grand Isle, Lamoille, Orange, Orleans, and Washington are specifically eligible for this assistance. Hazard mitigation measures statewide will also be eligible for federal funding on a cost-sharing basis. William F. Roy has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas, and additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.